[{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_8_1","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":8,"verse":1,"text":"into their midst as the land, as an eagle against the house of the Lord, because they have transgressed my covenant, and have sinned against my law.","searchKeywords":["into","their","midst","the","land","eagle","against","house","lord","because","they","have","transgressed","covenant","and","sinned","law"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_8_2","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":8,"verse":2,"text":"They shall soon cry out to me, , O God, we know thee.","searchKeywords":["they","shall","soon","cry","out","god","know","thee"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_8_3","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":8,"verse":3,"text":"For Israel has turned away from good things; they have pursued an enemy.","searchKeywords":["for","israel","has","turned","away","from","good","things","they","have","pursued","enemy"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_8_4","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":8,"verse":4,"text":"They have made kings for themselves, but not by me: they have ruled, but they did not make it known to me: their silver and their gold they have made images to themselves, that they might be destroyed.","searchKeywords":["they","have","made","kings","for","themselves","but","not","ruled","did","make","known","their","silver","and","gold","images","that","might","destroyed"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_8_5","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":8,"verse":5,"text":"Cast off thy calf, O Samaria; mine anger is kindled against them: how long will they be unable to purge themselves in Israel?","searchKeywords":["cast","off","thy","calf","samaria","mine","anger","kindled","against","them","how","long","will","they","unable","purge","themselves","israel"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_8_6","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":8,"verse":6,"text":"Whereas the workman made it, and it is not God; wherefore thy calf, Samaria, was a deceiver:","searchKeywords":["whereas","the","workman","made","and","not","god","wherefore","thy","calf","samaria","was","deceiver"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_8_7","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":8,"verse":7,"text":"for they sowed blighted , and their destruction shall await them, a sheaf of corn that avails not to make meal; and even if it should produce it, strangers shall devour it.","searchKeywords":["for","they","sowed","blighted","and","their","destruction","shall","await","them","sheaf","corn","that","avails","not","make","meal","even","should","produce","strangers","devour"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_8_8","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":8,"verse":8,"text":"Israel is swallowed up: now is he become among the nations as a worthless vessel.","searchKeywords":["israel","swallowed","now","become","among","the","nations","worthless","vessel"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_8_9","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":8,"verse":9,"text":"For they have gone up to the Assyrians: Ephraim has been strengthened against himself; they loved gifts.","searchKeywords":["for","they","have","gone","the","assyrians","ephraim","has","been","strengthened","against","himself","loved","gifts"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_8_10","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":8,"verse":10,"text":"Therefore shall they be delivered to the nations: now I will receive them, and they shall cease a little to anoint a king and princes.","searchKeywords":["therefore","shall","they","delivered","the","nations","now","will","receive","them","and","cease","little","anoint","king","princes"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_8_11","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":8,"verse":11,"text":"Because Ephraim has multiplied altars, beloved altars are become sins to him.","searchKeywords":["because","ephraim","has","multiplied","altars","beloved","are","become","sins","him"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_8_12","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":8,"verse":12,"text":"I will write down a multitude for him; but his statutes are accounted strange things, the beloved altars.","searchKeywords":["will","write","down","multitude","for","him","but","his","statutes","are","accounted","strange","things","the","beloved","altars"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_8_13","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":8,"verse":13,"text":"For if they should offer a sacrifice, and eat flesh, the Lord will not accept them: now will he remember their iniquities, and will take vengeance on their sins: they have returned to Egypt, and they shall eat unclean things among the Assyrians.","searchKeywords":["for","they","should","offer","sacrifice","and","eat","flesh","the","lord","will","not","accept","them","now","remember","their","iniquities","take","vengeance","sins","have","returned","egypt","shall","unclean","things","among","assyrians"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_8_14","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":8,"verse":14,"text":"And Israel has forgotten him that made him, and they have built fanes, and Juda has multiplied walled cities: but I will send fire on his cities, and it shall devour their foundations.","searchKeywords":["and","israel","has","forgotten","him","that","made","they","have","built","fanes","juda","multiplied","walled","cities","but","will","send","fire","his","shall","devour","their","foundations"]}]